definition.value: A protein-DNA complex that forms at the origin of replication during the initial step of DNA replication and allows the origin to become competent, or 'licensed', for replication.

The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the pre-replicative complex, a protein-DNA complex that forms at the origin of replication during the initial step of DNA replication and allows the origin to become competent, or 'licensed', for replication.
A protein-DNA complex that forms at the bacterial oriC during the initial step of DNA replication and allows the origin to become competent, or 'licensed', for replication.

label.value: pre-replicative complex assembly involved in bacterial-type DNA replication

definition.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form the bacterial pre-replicative complex, a protein-DNA complex that forms at the bacterial oriC during the initial step of DNA replication and allows the origin to become competent, or 'licensed', for replication.

A double ring-shaped structure that forms at the medial cortex at the onset of cytokinesis -  composed of members of the conserved family of filament forming proteins called septins as well as septin-associated proteins.
Catalysis of the reaction -  thiocyanate (SCN-) + hydrogen peroxide (H2O2) -eq- hypothiocyanite (OSCN-) + 2 H2O. Catalyzes the hydrogen peroxide oxidation of thiocyanate.

An mRNA methyltransferase complex that catalyzes the post-transcriptional methylation of adenosine to form N6-methyladenosine (m6A). In budding yeast, the MIS complex consists of Mum2p, Ime4p and Slz1p. In vertebrates, the complex consists of METTL3, METTL14 and WTAP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  formate + a quinone -eq- CO2 + a quinol.

A multi-protein complex containing at least the T-cell receptor complex and the LAT (linker for activation of T cells) scaffold protein. Also contains a variety of signaling proteins including co-receptors, kinases, phosphatases and adaptors such as CD8. Connects events on the plasma membrane to distal signaling cascades to ultimately modulate T cell biology.

Combining with a short neuropeptide F and transmitting the signal within the cell to initiate a change in cell activity. Short neuropeptide F is an arthropod peptide of less than 28 residues (as small as 8-10 residues in some species) with a C-terminal RFamide or LRFamide.

Combining with a pyrokinin and transmitting the signal within the cell to induce a change in cell activity. Pyrokinins are a group of insect neuropeptides that share the common C-terminal pentapeptide sequence Phe-X-Pro-Arg-Leu-NH2 (X -eq- S, T, K, A, or G). They play a central role in diverse physiological processes including stimulation of gut motility, production and release of sex pheromones, diapause, and pupariation.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate, which promotes unfolding of protein substrates, and channel opening of the core proteasome.
Catalysis of the reaction -  arachidonate + O(2) -eq- (5Z,8S,9E,11Z,14Z)-8-hydroperoxyicosa-5,9,11,14-tetraenoate.

label.value: anchored component of cell outer membrane

definition.value: The component of the cell outer membrane consisting of the gene products that are tethered to the membrane only by a covalently attached anchor, such as a lipid group embedded in the membrane. Gene products with peptide sequences that are embedded in the membrane are excluded from this grouping.

label.value: anchored component of periplasmic side of cell outer membrane

definition.value: The component of the cell outer membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that are tethered to the periplasmic side of membrane by only a covalently attached anchor, embedded in the periplasmic side of the membrane only.

A mycolic acid-rich cell outer membrane containing a lipid bilayer and long-chain mycolic acids (hydroxylated branched-chain fatty acids) that are covalently linked to the cell wall peptidoglycan via an arabinogalactan network. Found in mycobacteria and related genera (e.g. corynebacteria).
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + histone H3 L-lysine (position 14) -eq- CoA + histone H3 N6-acetyl-L-lysine (position 14).
A protein complex that can catalyze the acetylation of lysine at position 14 in histone H3.

A protein complex that can catalyze the acetylation of lysine at position 14 in histone H3, and contains Mst2 as the catalytic subunit. In fission yeast, contains at least Mst2, Nto1, Ptf2, Ptf1 and Eaf6.
A trimeric protein complex containing a H-NS homodimer and a Cnu monomer. In bacteria, this complex negatively regulates transcription of a range of genes.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + oxalate -eq- acetate + oxalyl-CoA.

label.value: intrinsic component of mycolate outer membrane

definition.value: The component of the mycolate outer membrane consisting of the gene products that have some covalently attached part (e.g. peptide sequence or GPI anchor) which spans or is embedded in one or both leaflets of the membrane.

label.value: integral component of mycolate outer membrane

definition.value: The component of the mycolate outer membrane consisting of the gene products that have some part that penetrates at least one leaflet of the membrane bilayer. This component includes gene products that are buried in the bilayer with no exposure outside the bilayer.

label.value: extrinsic component of mycolate outer membrane

definition.value: The component of mycolate outer membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that are loosely bound to one of its surfaces, but not integrated into the hydrophobic region.

label.value: extrinsic component of external side of mycolate outer membrane

definition.value: The component of mycolate membrane consisting of gene products and protein complexes that are loosely bound to its external surface, but not integrated into the hydrophobic region.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + 4 isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- 4 diphosphate + all-trans-heptaprenyl diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (2E,6E)-farnesyl diphosphate + 3 isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- 3 diphosphate + all-trans-hexaprenyl diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O-phospho-L-serine + H2O -lt--eq--gt- L-serine + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O-phospho-D-serine + H2O -lt--eq--gt- L-serine + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ditrans,octacis-undecaprenyl phosphate + GDP-alpha-D-mannose -eq- D-mannosyl undecaprenyl phosphate+ GDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  all-trans-undecaprenyl phosphate + GDP-alpha-D-mannose -eq- D-mannosyl undecaprenyl phosphate + GDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosylcobinamide + GTP -eq- adenosylcobinamide phosphate + GDP + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosylcobinamide + ATP -eq- adenosylcobinamide phosphate + ADP + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + CMP -eq- ADP + CDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + dCMP -eq- ADP + dCDP.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + undecaprenol + all-trans-undecaprenyl phosphate + ADP + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  di-trans, octa-cis-undecaprenol + ATP -eq- di-trans,octa-cis-undecaprenyl phosphate + ADP + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ethylnitronate + FMNH(2) + O(2) -eq- acetaldehyde + FMN + H(2)O + H(+) + nitrite.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently and non-covalently with a polymer of ubiquitin formed by linkages between lysine residues at position 48 of the ubiquitin monomers.
An Isw1 complex that binds DNA and has nucleosome-stimulated ATPase activity. In S. cerevisiae, contains an Isw1p ATPase subunit in complex with Ioc3p.
An Isw1 complex that binds DNA and has nucleosome-stimulated ATPase activity. In S. cerevisiae, contains an Isw1p ATPase subunit in complex with Ioc2p and Ioc4p.
Catalysis of the reaction -  glycerol 3-phosphate + NADP+ -eq- glycerone phosphate + H+ + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + H2O + oxaloacetate -eq- citrate + CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-pantolactone + NADP+ -eq- 2-dehydropantolactone + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the transfer of protons from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + H+(in) --gt- ADP + phosphate + H+(out).
Catalysis of the reaction -  3'-phosphoadenylyl sulfate + dermatan -eq- adenosine 3',5'-bisphosphate + dermatan 6'-sulfate.
The self-renewing division of a neuronal stem cell.
The end of a microtubule that does not preferentially grow (polymerize).
An endosomal sorting complex required for transport.
A protein complex that has growth factor activity.
